      },
      "date": "2015-03-19 07:29:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI suspect that we previously had debugging in this function, but we removed it because it was too verbose for any normal DLMTRACE debugging needs.\n\nNot that I'm insisting on it, but have you looked at whether kernel tracepoints are a viable option here?  That is something that we will eventually need for upstream acceptance, so it makes sense to figure out whether it is usable for us or not.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
